"{\"statement\": \"Task: Given a forest with n vertices, where each tree is an undirected acyclic graph with k vertices and k - 1 edges, and each vertex has a unique id from 1 to n representing a relative of PolandBall. For each Ball i, the id of its most distant relative living on the same tree is given. If there are several such vertices, we only know the value of the one with the smallest id among those. Find the number of trees in the forest.\\n\\nInput: The input consists of two lines. The first line contains a single integer n (1 \\u2264 n \\u2264 104) representing the number of Balls living in the forest. The second line contains a sequence p1, p2, ..., pn of length n, where (1 \\u2264 pi \\u2264 n) holds and pi denotes the most distant from Ball i relative living on the same tree.\\n\\nOutput: The output should be a single integer representing the number of trees in the forest.\\n\\nConstraints: The input sequence p corresponds to some valid forest.\", \"editorial\": \"\", \"tag\": \"['Tree algorithms', 'Graph algorithms', 'Graph traversal', 'Spanning trees']\", \"difficulties\": \"EASY\", \"source\": \"codeforces\", \"url\": \"https://codeforces.com/problemset/problem/755/C\", \"sample_test_cases\": [{\"input\": \"3 1\\n2 3\\n\", \"output\": \"3\\n\"}, {\"input\": \"2 0\\n\", \"output\": \"1\"}, {\"input\": \"3 0\\n\", \"output\": \"1\"}, {\"input\": \"4 3\\n3 1\\n1 2\\n2 4\\n\", \"output\": \"1\\n\"}, {\"input\": \"1 0\\n\", \"output\": \"1\"}, {\"input\": \"18 2\\n9 17\\n1 18\\n\", \"output\": \"1\\n\"}, {\"input\": \"3 2\\n1 2\\n2 3\\n\", \"output\": \"1\\n\"}, {\"input\": \"5 4\\n1 2\\n1 3\\n1 4\\n3 5\\n\", \"output\": \"1\\n\"}, {\"input\": \"10000 1\\n1725 10000\\n\", \"output\": \"2\\n\"}, {\"input\": \"5 1\\n4 5\\n\", \"output\": \"2\\n\"}, {\"input\": \"5 4\\n1 3\\n1 4\\n4 2\\n5 2\\n\", \"output\": \"2\\n\"}, {\"input\": \"2 1\\n1 2\\n\", \"output\": \"1\\n\"}, {\"input\": \"10 3\\n2 8\\n5 9\\n6 10\\n\", \"output\": \"3\\n\"}, {\"input\": \"6 5\\n1 4\\n2 3\\n3 4\\n4 5\\n5 6\\n\", \"output\": \"1\\n\"}, {\"input\": \"5 3\\n1 2\\n3 4\\n4 5\\n\", \"output\": \"1\\n\"}]}"